This is the first Spanish-language article set. It covers all seven Cluster 1 topics from Master Plan §11, built directly from the five Lane-1 pain points in §4, plus the hub FAQ section for /es/compradores/. Every article was written in Spanish from the start — nothing here is a translation of an English draft, and Cluster 4 (the English mirror) will be drafted separately later, at which point each pair gets its hreflang links. Until then these pages self-reference as es only.

**RESPA compliance (five of seven articles touch financing):** every lending fact below was verified in July 2026 against the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau — including CFPB's native Spanish pages at consumerfinance.gov/es, which are the citation links used, so readers land on Spanish-language government resources. No interest rate appears anywhere, numeric or implied. No closing-cost dollar figures or ranges. No qualification predictions. The agent-not-lender statement appears in-context on every financing article; its locked Spanish rendering is defined below and should be reused verbatim on all future /es/ financing content.

